    "summary": "The user, acting as a debate coach, asks the assistant to \"steelman\" arguments for stricter immigration enforcement and then requests common rebuttals to those arguments to prepare students for a competitive round. The assistant provides nuanced, philosophically grounded arguments for the enforcement side (citing social contract theory) and then provides a summary of the opposing humanitarian and economic arguments.",
